{"type":"message","id":"4a129abb","parentId":"c1559cf8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:34:33.076Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h1sfqmtaign8_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3474\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[master 4855af5] pulse: 2026-03-24 123414\n 5 files changed, 177 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 123414.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 123318.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 123414 - CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). A compression experiment is needed to validate CFI-weighting as superior to pure frequency-counting.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"dawn-dune","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3474\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[master 4855af5] pulse: 2026-03-24 123414\n 5 files changed, 177 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 123414.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 123318.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 123414 - CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). A compression experiment is needed to validate CFI-weighting as superior to pure frequency-counting.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370073072}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee111b20","parentId":"4a129abb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:34:33.079Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h1sfqmtaign8_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 123318\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. Key findings from this session include:\r\n   - Architecture cross-analysis complete\r\n   - Gap-decay synthesis complete\r\n   - LLM-augmented pulse working\r\n   - CFI Analysis complete with new doc `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\n3. Pending items include:\r\n   - CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n   - Implement CFI filtering\r\n   - Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n   - Wire Breakaway to TemporalAttention backend\r\n   - Design actual compression network\r\n\r\n4. Key insight: Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7) - these are the true causal anchors\r\n\r\nSince no mutations were applied last cycle and the CFI analysis revealed that most frequency-invariants are just noise (44.8% have CFI=0), the most impactful next step would be to start the CFI-weighted compression experiment that was flagged as \"next\" in the CFI results.\r\n\r\nThe experiment should compare:\r\n- Frequency baseline (current approach)\r\n- CFI-weighted approach (prioritize high-CFI invariants)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete next step that advances the pending work on compression.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). Only 5.7% are true causal anchors. The next logical step is to run the planned CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether filtering by CFI improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares frequency-baseline vs CFI-weighted invariant selection, measuring prediction coherence across pulses.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24 1231\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nFiltering invariants by CFI ( Causality Fraction Index ) will improve next-pulse prediction coherence compared to frequency-only baseline, because high-CFI invariants represent true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Selection\r\n- Select top-N invariants by frequency count\r\n- No CFI filtering\r\n- This is the current approach\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Selection\r\n- Option A: Filter out CFI < 0.5, then rank by frequency\r\n- Option B: Score = frequency * CFI, rank by composite score\r\n- Option C: Select top-N by CFI alone (regardless of frequency)\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Prediction Coherence:** How well selected invariants predict next pulse content\r\n- **Compression Ratio:** tokens_saved / original_tokens\r\n- **Signal Retention:** % of true research trajectory content preserved\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract invariants from recent pulses (last 10)\r\n```\r\nPULSE_DIR=\"pulses\"\r\nINVARIANTS_FILE=\"research/invariants_pool.md\"\r\nCFI_CACHE=\"research/cfi_cache.json\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Compute CFI for each invariant\r\n```python\r\n# For each invariant:\r\n# 1. Count appearances across pulses\r\n# 2. Count frequency variations (shifts)\r\n# 3. CFI = 1 - (variations / appearances)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Run both selection strategies\r\n- Collect top 20 invariants from each method\r\n- Compare overlap and divergence\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Measure prediction accuracy\r\n- Use selected invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n- Score predictions against actual pulse\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted selection will:\r\n- Remove ~45% noise (CFI=0 invariants)\r\n- Preserve research trajectory (CFI>0.7)\r\n- Improve prediction coherence by eliminating false signals\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD after execution)\r\n\r\n| Metric | Frequency-Basis | CFI-Weighted | Delta |\r\n|--------|-----------------|--------------|-------|\r\n| Invariants Selected | - | - | - |\r\n| Noise (CFI=0) | - | - | - |\r\n| True Anchors (CFI>=0.7) | - | - | - |\r\n| Prediction Coherence | - | - | - |\r\n| Compression Ratio | - | - | - |\r\n\r\n## Execution Log\r\n- [ ] Extract invariants from pulses/\r\n- [ ] Compute CFI for each\r\n- [ ] Run baseline selection\r\n- [ ] Run CFI-weighted selection  \r\n- [ ] Compare predictions\r\n- [ ] Document results\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:33:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370073076}}
