{"type":"message","id":"c1365b35","parentId":"e4898edc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:34:46.872Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse:\n1. Completed CFI analysis (revealed 44.8% noise, only 5.7% true causal anchors)\n2. Proposed a new experiment file `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md`\n3. Committed the changes\n4. Moved the previous proposal to rejected\n\nLet me summarize this for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"69dbf086e25e08b1f90ed93925350fbdfe1bc90248d969b56b7f109f1d99a8f0"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse 2026-03-24 12:34 — Complete**\n\n**CFI Analysis Results:** The big finding this cycle. Of the frequency-invariants tracked across recent pulses:\n- **44.8% are pure noise** (CFI=0 — appear often but never vary, so they're metaprogramming artifacts, not real signals)\n- **~5.7% are true causal anchors** (CFI ≥ 0.7 — actually track meaningful research trajectory)\n- The rest (49.5%) fall in between\n\n**Mutation Applied:** Created `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` — a structured experiment to validate whether CFI-weighted invariant selection outperforms the current frequency-only approach. It proposes comparing three selection strategies (filter by CFI threshold, composite score, CFI-alone ranking) against baseline on prediction coherence and compression metrics.\n\n**Commit:** `4855af5` — 5 files changed, +177/-103 lines. Previous pending proposal moved to `mutations/rejected/`.\n\n**Status:** The experiment file is ready but not yet executed. Next pulse should run it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1839,"output":313,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14289,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774370076669}}
